element.name: Weir is the cache? by lolly810 and l4flare, Traditional Cache (2/2.5)
element.long-description:
"Weir is the cache" can be found at a weir on the north side of the river Liffey in an area known as the Strawberry Beds in Dublin 15.
Parking is available at The Wren's Nest pub located on the R109, this road is quite busy so take care if walking.
The weir is a very popular location during sunny days where people come to fish and swim, so beware of muggles.
The cache itself is a small brown lunchbox container placed in some undergrowth. Please take caution when the water levels are high as the area around may become slippery. You do not have to cross the river or enter the water to retrieve the cache.
It is important to note that due to many trees in this area the coordinates can be off slightly.
element.encoded-hints: In a bush to the left of an outlook

ul.li:
2010-06-10T19:00:00Z : Didn't find it by rooske
We spent well over one hour looking for this one with no success. The best reading our gps was 8 meters .We met Theswerve also hunting for this one, we had a great chat with him it was a very enjoyable evening
This entry was edited by rooske on Thursday, 17 June 2010 at 12:48:46.

2010-06-07T19:00:00Z : Write note by lolly810
Wahey we have our FTF well done Besiebob and Moyle, thought no one would find it... so proud of you two [:D]

2010-06-07T19:00:00Z : Found it by Besiebob
Didn't expect to find it in view of previous logs. After searching for about an hour, I put away the GPS and used the old grey matter. With a bit of lateral thinking and logic I looked to the left, took a step forward and could just about see the cache while still a few feet away from it. This has been a very satisfying find! T.F.T.F. [:D] [:D] [:D]

2010-06-07T16:33:05Z : Found it by moyle
I know weir the cache is, it's weir it was hidden!!! Good one this, we spent about an hour looking before I heard a shout from Besiebob. I thought she has fallen in the river but no!!! she had found the cache. [:D]

2010-06-06T19:00:00Z : Write note by lolly810
[A little hint here if you want]
Keep left and follow that path
[Really hope someone finds it soon [;)]]
